{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Lr9mR5fXdstowuvCAd1Gx9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I found the bug. The OCR_SUBSTITUTIONS map has `\"Í\": [\"i\"]` (uppercase Í), but in `repairOcrWord` we check `OCR_SUBSTITUTIONS[lower[i]]` where `lower[i]` would be `\"í\"` (lowercase Í, U+00ED). The key `\"Í\"` (U+00CD) would never match `\"í\"` (U+00ED).\n\nThe fix: change `\"Í\": [\"i\"]` to `\"í\": [\"i\"]` in the map. The OCR_ARTIFACT_PATTERN checks against the original `word` (before lowercasing), so it correctly catches `Í`. But the positions loop checks `lower[i]`, so the map key needs to be the lowercase version.\n\n\nThe inverted exclamation mark `\"¡\"` doesn't have a case variant, so `.toLowerCase()` leaves it unchanged and the map key is already correct. Now I'll apply the fix.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3823,"cache_read_input_tokens":29229,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3823},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f9013127-e6f1-45ef-82dd-139400a6a801","uuid":"96d4c119-de78-4604-af3e-71350892abd0"}
