{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01X5eTVKwvzN8a51L5J4tbqx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, but also the OCR_ARTIFACT_PATTERN still uses `Í` (uppercase). That's checked against the original `word` (before lowercasing). For a word like `\"GRILÍED\"`, `OCR_ARTIFACT_PATTERN.test(\"GRILÍED\")` would match `Í`. Good.\n\nBut if the artifact appears in lowercase context like `\"grilíed\"`, the pattern `/[0-9¡Í€]/` would NOT match because it checks for `Í` (uppercase) not `í` (lowercase). So we should also add `í` to the pattern.\n\n\nActually, looking at the existing `normalizeOcrTitle` code, the ALL_CAPS branch handles `Í` with a replacement, but the mixed-case handling only deals with `¡`. Since dictionary repair lowercases everything before checking, I need to think about whether `í` would actually appear in that context—the existing code suggests `Í` is expected in uppercase contexts, not lowercase ones.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":551,"cache_read_input_tokens":33052,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":551},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f9013127-e6f1-45ef-82dd-139400a6a801","uuid":"520d60d2-f9de-460c-afd2-8780a6c1a141"}
